data.title: Charles Chester (rugby)
data.meta_description: Charles T. Chester was an English rugby union, and professional rugby league footballer who played in the 1930s, 1940s and 1950s. He played club level rugby union (RU) for Sandal RUFC. and club level rugby league (RL) for Wakefield Trinity, as a prop, or second-row, i.e. number 8 or 10, or 11 or 12, during the era of contested scrums.
